9 An Act relating to emergency management; stating role
of government in emergencies; stating scope of
10 government authority; prohibiting certain actions;
creating felony offense; listing additional
11 punishments; providing for codification; and
providing an effective date.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 683.24C of Title 63, unless
17 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. The constitutional role of government personnel, elected and
19 employed, and all government agencies, during emergencies and
20 disasters, is to aid residents of this state.
21 B. All government personnel, elected and employed, and all
22 government agencies have no authority to subvert the constitutional
23 rights of the residents of this state, even during times of
24 emergency or disaster.
