1 C. All government personnel, elected and employed, and all
2 government agencies are prohibited from enacting or imposing any
3 actions subverting the constitutional rights of the residents of
4 this state, even during times of emergency or disaster.
5 D. Examples of actions that shall be considered subversions of
6 constitutional rights shall include:
7 1. Requiring or compelling residents to receive a shot,
8 vaccine, inoculation, or any other medical treatment;
9 2. Requiring or compelling residents to wear a mask or medical
10 device, with the exception of first responders and medical
11 personnel;
12 3. Restricting any right to medical treatment based on
13 vaccination status, confiscating personal property, restricting
14 constitutional freedoms, or restraining a patient involuntarily
15 unless otherwise required by law;
16 4. Requiring or compelling residents to show any documentation
17 of vaccination status that was not already required by law prior to
18 the emergency or disaster;
19 5. Imposing any unconstitutional law, regulation, or
20 restriction on businesses, churches, organizations, or residents
21 that was not codified in law prior to the emergency or disaster;
22 6. Restricting the rights of residents to exercise free speech,
23 to peaceably assemble and gather in large groups, and to petition
24 government for the redress of grievances, and restricting any other
