1 Firs t Amendment right in any way that was not codified in law prior
2 to the emergency or disaster;
3 7. Restricting the rights of residents to exercise any Second
4 Amendment right in any way that was not codified in law prior to the
5 emergency or disaster; and
6 8. Restricting the rights of residents to travel freely in any
7 way that was not codified in law prior to the emergency or disaster.
8 E. Any government official, elected or employed, who violates
9 the provisions of this section shall, upon conviction, be guilty of
10 a felony punishable by imprisonment in the custody of the Department
11 of Corrections for not more than five (5) years, a fine not more
12 than Fifty Thousand Dollars ($50,000.00), or by both such
13 imprisonment and fine. The convicted government official shall also
14 be subject to:
15 1. Removal from his or her office or position;
16 2. Prohibition from holding any future elected or public
17 office;
18 3. A fine of Ten Thousand Dollars ($10,000.00) per violation;
19 and
20 4. Personal assumption of all liability where the government
21 would otherwise be liable.
22 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
